04/02/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- At least four people drowned and 12 went missing when a boat carrying illegal immigrants capsized near the Greek island of Samos on Saturday (3 February). Three people managed to swim ashore and alert the authorities. Rescuers found four bodies. Two people drowned and five went missing in a similar accident near Samos two weeks ago. Officials have not disclosed the nationalities of the latest victims, but local media reported that they were from countries in the Middle East. (DPA - 03/02/07)
